caption: Place is great, food is always on point. Have been to other Thai places in Hyde Park never as good as Siam.
This place is wonderful and so are the people! Great tasting food and amazing service.

I really loved the dishes and customer service, great location nearby to my home. The employees are always friendly. Would recommend to others.
Great food
Nice environment and very amiable service. The meals were crisp and delicious. Will absolutely recommend this restaurant to friends. Fair prices and generous meals. Keep up the great work.
Had shrimp fried rice and I really enjoyed it to the fullest!! Definitely be back!
Delicious, good price, good service :)
So good, a hidden gem in Hyde Park we love it and they have very nice people working there!!!
I get to eat here a lot since I work in the area. I have to say their service is always great and they keep the spot neat constantly. Pricing is convenient and they serve sizeable portions.
This place is one of my favorite places to go to eat in Hyde Park because it hold such great memories! The decor could use a little sprucing up though.
The catfish was delicious!
Quality of good is better when u eat in.

The service is awful!!! I ordered Shrimp Pad Thai with no peanuts for delivery. When it arrived, it was loaded with peanuts.  I called and asked for it to be replaced and I was given a hard time. The second delivery came and the food was terrible. It was gummy and had no flavor. I called back and asked for a refund because I couldn't eat it and I was told that there was nothing he could do. They had sent the driver out twice and they were not going to send him back. Terrible service, rude people.
My favorite Thai restaurant in Hyde Park. Their noodle dishes, soup of the day, and egg rolls are very good.
Great food

Out of all the Thai places in the area, we prefer this one because of its reasonable prices, lunch specials, and more authentic flavors. My favorite dish is the duck red curry. The pad Thai (husbands favorite) is not too sweet, like at other places.
Quiet atmosphere has a lunch menu up to about 4oclock, good food A lot of people did carry out so it wasn't crowded, nice service
Amazing food with big portions!

That roach gave me “I’m home”...like he knew the ins and outs of the table ...which lets me know he WAS home and likely not alone. I’m not going back.

Fantastic food, friendly and quick service.  Dont let the interior of this restaurant fool you.  What they lack in class they more than make up for in quality and price point.

Great place, good prices and nice service

I got their lunch special (comes with soup of the day, egg roll, and an entree with rice) and there was not one bad item in my bag! The soup was a fresh and delicious vegetable soup, filled with broccoli, snow peas, bean sprouts, mushrooms, carrots, cabbage, etc. Filled me up and had a deep, rich broth! Egg roll is one of the very few that I have had that were freshly made and without an awful aftertaste from using vegetables refrigerated for too long or too close to their expiry date. I chose the basil tofu for my entree and the tofu was lightly fried but still firm and had lots of veggies and sauce to go along with the rice. Run by blunt, but still very nice women! I definitely WILL be coming back.
authentic
Delicious fresh food. To those complaining about wait,  stop please! Many of items are made to order. Even the egg rolls are awesome!  Staff is friendly and kind.
It was wonderful!!! Great lunch specials!! Will be back!!
I like their lunches a lot

Terrible delivery service with rude and incompetent staff. We ordered through Grub hub, the estimated delivery time was one hour. After waiting an hour an fifteen minutes I called the restaurant to check the status twice, each time the man who answered gave evasive answers and when I asked him for a refund he said to talk to the driver. When the driver finally arrived one hour late, he said to contact the restaurant. Needless to say we did not take the food and it was a nightmare just to get a refund. Avoid ordering from this place at all cost if you can.

This is hands down the best thai food in Hyde Park! Make sure to get their lunch special- at only $8.95, it comes with soup, egg roll and a generous portion of an entree. My favorites are their panang and massaman curries with tofu. Please note that hospitality and service are not their forte, so don't go there if that's what you look for in a restaurant, but I've heard that this is a pretty good indication that it's an authentic thai place!

I'm a regular here They know me. I'm.kim.its the hehiest tasotes option. Perhaps they can have like a customer appreciation card .like by five get 1 free type of deal. They have really healthy Thai sould food. Food is fresh and good. A bit pricey though. The fried chicken wings are way better than poeyes or sharks
Great thai food
Great pad thai and panang curry. Best thai on 55th.
Best Bangkok Chicken in the city. I know, I've looked.
Still my favorite Thai place in the city. The spicy, coconut milk soup is delicious, so are the fried rice, and all the curry dishes.

(Translated by Google) It is a restaurant that sells Thai rice dishes casually. The menu is generally inexpensive and tasty. It is recommended to stir fried rice rather than fried rice.  (Original) 태국의 집밥을 가성비있게 파는 식당. 메뉴가 전반적으로 저렴하며 맛도 있다. 볶음밥보다는 볶음면을 추천하는 편이고 세트로 식사를 하면 양이 조금 많을 수도 있다.

Always fresh and delicious. Great flavors and a variety of options for everyone. My absolute favorite! Definitely love the specials as you get an egg roll, soup and for the dinner special-  a salad with your entree. Please visit this staple in Hyde Park.
Didn't provide rice with my carry out order. Who does that?
Great pad thai
Mean and slow service, the waiter refused to give me the Wi-Fi password. Expensive prices for mediocre food quality. I wouldn't come back again
Wanted to like this place. The pork satay was a good start to the meal. The other dishes were ok. Not a fan of the pad thai. Too sweet, lacked flavor and the noodle is over cooked.
Best Thai Ever
Very excellent. Lots of food, all of it delicious. The peanut sauce is to die for. Ask for it with the pad Thai, you won't regret it.
Forgot rice in order, plus the sesame chicken  was like a soup. Worst food ever. Even the chicken fried rice was not the best.  Skip this place
The customer service was ok. The food was good. Portions were small, for the cost. Not much meat in the rice.
The food was very good and tasty. I ordered he Bangkok Chicken and it was a good portion and filled me up for a low price.

I have ordered from Siam on countless occasions. However, today is the second time I ordered their Pad Woon Sen w/chicken and was disappointed. The baby corn was noticeably sour and the noodles were old. In fact, although not an ingredient, pepper was added, probably to mask the taste.  My food was ordered through GrubHub and I did not feel up to going to their restaurant to complain; they know what they sold me. So, I'm done. I won't be ordering from them again.  There are other Thai restaurants in the area!  #DoBetter #StopDeceivingYourCustomers

The food is pretty good here but their service can be a hit or a miss. I've dined in and done takeout with relatively no issues. However, today was my first time attempting to order for delivery from their website. I live in Bronzville which in my opinoin is not too far from Hyde Park but anyway...  I placed my order online, *at no time was I prompted on their website that there were delivery location restrictions-in fact my delivery fee increased once I typed in the address. Also, I order from Hyde Park resturants frequently without any issue. Immediately after I placed my order I recieved a phone call from the restaurant. And the man very rudly asked me where was my street located. He then went on to say that he had never heard of my street name and he's lived in Hyde Park for 30 years. He only delivers locally in Hyde Park. So I said, okay can you refund my delivery fee and then he tells me "you have to call the website. okay? Okay goodbye"  While I was able to initation a refund with relative ease from the company they use to order online, the way the man handled the entire situation was very rude. I would have even been willing to pick my order up had the service I recieved been better.
Decided to eat elsewhere because it was filthy inside. You could smell the restroom from the dining area!
Eat here regularly. Crab Rangoon is best in Hyde Park!

My pic doesn’t do it justice, the tofu fried rice was delish!  Whenever I walk past I see lots of people in here so I wanted to see what brought people in. I ordered to go and was told 20 minutes, but when I got there I had to wait 20 more minutes for my food. It’s really good so I stopped being upset once I got home. The egg rolls are perfectly crunchy, they use a lot of tofu for the fried rice and it is seasoned really great. The Thai iced tea is good too, not too sweet and not too strong. The interior isn’t as pretty as like Snail Queen, but you’re there for the food not the ambiance anyway lol. The menu is pretty diverse so everyone will find something yummy here, and I would say the food is worth the price.
Very good tastes and quantity, i like very much !
Waiters a little bit rude but the food is awesome, rations could be more generous.
Awesome food! Loved it.
Love the food & the people are great
There are a couple of (more pricey) thai spots in Hyde Park, but Siam is hands down the best. Inexpensive and consistently delicious. Staff is friendly, BYOB, lots of vegan options. Love it.
Best Thai restaurant in Hyde Park

So I almost walked out for the water alone... But was like, "maybe I'm tripping"... Ordered Pad Thai and shrimp... My shrimp was over cooked and the tails were left on... It was entirely too sweet, I couldn't stomach eating it... I told him I didn't want to pay because I had an entire plate of food left and didn't want to take it with me... He said I couldn't do that and I was like screw it I'll pay and threw it away

Ordered over the phone for pickup. Service was fast, super friendly, and my tofu pad ke mao was delicious! (a bit too oily for my liking but not worth taking a star away for) Would definitely come back here again! (P.S.: the tofu pad thai was also pretty good)
Best Thai on the block. Pad Se ew was fresh and tasty, not swimming in sauce and slimy like some you get. Pad thai was legit as well. Will come back.
My wife and I wanted an authentic Thai experience. We were not disappointed. Pleasant and efficient staff and excellent food.
Pretty good. More authentic than a lot of other places.
The basil chicken rice is delectable. The basil chicken is okayish. The place is small and cozy. Customer service is not up to the mark.
Yr crazy not to eat here
Very beautiful place and spirits....excellent food
I enjoyed my meal here, but it took them an extra 30 minutes after I got my food to get my friend's meal out. (Actually they had forgotten to even make it.) Was disappointed in the service.
Good food
Good food
The food is really good, the staff is friendly, and the atmosphere is comfortable and quiet.
Definitely the best of the three Thai restaurant options in Hyde Park. We take all of our guest seminar speakers there and the owner always treats us well. Definitely BYOB!
Thanks for giving us best food
I love the food here. I've dined in and ordered take-out. I find the restaurant very relaxed and homey and they've always my take-out order ready within 20 minutes.

Terrible service. Never ate here before, will never try to again. The food took two hours and ten minutes to arrive and the person on the phone was unhelpful, rude and generally incompetent.  I ordered delivery at 19:45 on a blustery Saturday night, about a mile away. The person on the phone didn't tell me how long the food would be and I neglected to ask, which I realized as the call disconnected. Didn't call back to ask as I figured it wasn't a big deal.  An hour and ten minutes later I called the restaurant back. The guy said the food was on its way. I asked how long it might be and he said that the driver was laden down with orders, and after asking for an estimate (we were hungry!) he said he'd ask the driver and call me back.  Ten minutes later I call the restaurant back (1:20 after initial order) and the guy tells me that I should have ordered pickup instead. After explaining that information would have been helpful as I placed the order he starts lecturing me about the weather, how the night was busy and that they only had two drivers on that night who currently had 5 or 7 orders each. At the end of this he says, "so sorry, OK?", repeating this as if to shoo me off the phone.  Two hours and ten minutes later (50 minutes after last contact with the restaurant, with the last estimate being "maybe 20 minutes") the driver calls me to indicate he's almost there. I inform him that we're no longer interested in the food. He replies "Oh, OK, cool" and hangs up the phone.  This was my first and last experience with Siam Thai Cuisine. They seem uninterested in my business.

The food is good, authentic Thai food. I really enjoy getting the Basil Chicken (spicy). Prices for the food is inexpensive. I been to a few Thai restaurants in Hyde Park area. And I would say that the hole in the restaurant is better than majority of Thaj restaurants in the area.
Okay food kind of greasy
The food is beyond amazing, I would dine there again!
A nice place! Great food at a good price!
Food is okay. Service is okay. I had an okay time. Thus three stars.
Absolutely delicious. Amazing prices, staff is so friendly, small, intimate, and just incredible flavour.

This is not an authentic Thai restaurant. The smell when you walk in is stale. The padthai taste more like bonxao (Vietnamese noodles) the pad see ew is not very tasty. It lacks the good sweet soy sauce and fresh Chinese broccoli. Instead they use the normal broccoli and over cooked.

This is the best quality thai food in Hyde Park and a great option for take out and sit in. The prices are reasonable and the staff are great. The Pad Sie  Ew is a personal favorite of mine here and if you want to tweek the order and dishes, the staff will accomodate. Very deserving of patronage
Their food is good, but I've had better Thai. This is the best Thai in Hyde Park though.

The food was excellent; which is a shame, because the service was so horrible. I dined by myself, and ordered the dinner special (Tofu Pad Thai). The Cucumber Salad, Veggie Egg Rolls, and Tofu Curry soup; which where all very delicious (these items were serviced promptly). But, I waited a additional 35mins for my Entree to be serviced; as I watched people who arrived 20 mins later than I being served their Entrees before mine. I quietly said nothing, but resigned to not eat there again. Even something as small as my not receiving a "fortune cookie" at the end of my meal (as I observed them being given generously to other patrons) just annoyed me even more. I'm not certain what the reason may have been concerning these oversights, but it was disappointing to experience. Again I say; it's quite unfortunate that I had such bad service, because the food was very good.
Horrible chicken yellow curry. Whatever seasoning they use is GROSS!
The best thai food in Hyde Park.  They have the best spice and flavor.  The restaurant itself is fairly run down, but this is always my choice for take-out.

These past few month I been eating all there curry and its taste batter then before, I loved it. Few month ago it only taste like fish sauce and hot and now they have all the ingredient and I have not been smelling fish sauce, It perfects
Pad kee Mao, price and service was great!! I will return.

This is a quaint and quiet spot.  There's a plenty of room for whatever size party.  The service was a bit slow but the food was very good; I had Pad Siew with beef.  The Pad Thai tastes quite different from most according to others in my party.  Best to walk/bike here as parking is mostly metered.  Being in Hyde Park, it's directly accessible by bus also.

This place gave me  four fried shrimp with two sheets of flour bread, we're not crispy and fried vegetables with again two sheets of flour bread. Disgusting. They forgot the veggies do I had to go back for them. I waited a total of 30 minutes for a meal to go. I should have just gotten my money back.  The place also smelled and the lady who took my order was not knowledgable about the menu which did not help at all. I would never recommend this restaurant.

Love this place. I always get the Bangkok Chicken and it is consistently great. Delivery is also usually fast and my food comes hot, not warm. Haven't experimented much but the Bangkok Chicken alone is worth 5 stars.
Shrimp hot pot was delicious.
The Pad Siew with shrimp is one of my absolute favorite dishes in the world. I also love their mango sticky rice. Nice and relaxing restaurant.
Basil fried rice with roasted duck is delicious! This place has excellent food and very fast service. Love my neighborhood spot.

We started with the pot stickers and the fried squid which were both excellent. For our main dishes we had the Pad Thai with Chicken, Pad Thai with Shrimp, Sweet and Sour Tilapia, Siam Noodle and Pad Ped Talay. Every dish was fantastic, but the Pad Thai was out of this world.
Can't beat the basil chicken- it's nice n spicy. They are usually prompt and the prices are reasonable.
Could one experience better Thai in the city? No, we love this place and the food is fantastic coupled with a warm staff. I think you will have a wonderful time, go early and often.

I ordered food for takeout, it was an excellent experience. The food was made promptly and correctly. The staff was firendly and I enjoyed my short time in Siam Thai. I recommend the Thai Iced Tea and Massamon Curry.
I love the grilled cane'
One of my favorites.  The service here is amazing - johnny on the spot!  But the food?  Wow!  Great dishes, great flavors.  Never been disappointed here.  Highly recommended!!

This is the hidden jewel of 55th Streets Thai Row.  I had the ginger catfish, and it was divine!!!  It was coated with batter fried to a golden flaky crisp.  The veges were sauted with a ginger sauce that will put you in a trance.  This place is a must do again!!
Very authentic. Loved it.
